# Homework Autograding Pattern

All homework assignments use **point-based scoring** via GitHub Classroom's autograding actions.

## Critical: Command-grader strips environment variables

The `autograding-command-grader` only passes `PATH` and `HOME` to commands.
All custom env vars (SOURCE_DIR, BACKUP_DIR, etc.) are **invisible** inside grader commands.

**Workaround**: Write env vars to `/tmp/hw_env.sh` in the setup step (regular `run:`),
then `. /tmp/hw_env.sh` as the first line of every grader `command:`.

## Workflow Structure

```yaml
name: Autograding Tests
on: [push, workflow_dispatch]
permissions:
  actions: read
  contents: read
  checks: write
jobs:
  autograding:
    runs-on: ubuntu-22.04
    env:
      STUDENT_ID: ${{ github.actor }}
      SOME_DIR: /tmp/prefix_${{ github.actor }}
    steps:
      - uses: actions/checkout@v4
      - name: Setup test environment
        run: |
          # Persist env vars for the command-grader (it strips them)
          cat > /tmp/hw_env.sh << EOF
          export STUDENT_ID="$STUDENT_ID"
          export SOME_DIR="$SOME_DIR"
          EOF
          # ... install deps, create test fixtures ...
      - name: Test Name
        id: test-name  # kebab-case, used by reporter
        if: always()   # required on all tests after the first
        uses: classroom-resources/autograding-command-grader@v1
        with:
          test-name: Test Name
          command: |
            . /tmp/hw_env.sh
            # actual test commands here
          timeout: 2
          max-score: 30
      # ... more tests ...
      - name: Autograding Reporter
        uses: classroom-resources/autograding-grading-reporter@v1
        if: always()
        env:
          TEST-NAME_RESULTS: "${{steps.test-name.outputs.result}}"
        with:
          runners: test-name,other-test  # comma-separated step ids
```

## Key Rules

- Every test step uses `classroom-resources/autograding-command-grader@v1`
- **Every grader command MUST start with `. /tmp/hw_env.sh`** to restore env vars
- All tests except the first need `if: always()` so they run even if earlier tests fail
- The reporter step MUST have `if: always()` and map every test's `outputs.result`
- Reporter env var format: `STEP-ID_RESULTS` (step id uppercased, hyphens kept)
- `max-score` values across all tests should sum to 100
- Anti-copy: derive all paths/values from `${{ github.actor }}`

## Repo File Structure

Every homework directory must include:

- `script_name.sh` — student template with stubs
- `SOLUTION.sh` — instructor reference (gitignored)
- `.gitignore` — **must include `SOLUTION.sh`** so it stays out of student repos
- `.github/workflows/classroom.yml` — autograding workflow
- `README.md` — assignment spec
- `STUDENT_QUICKSTART.md` — quick-start guide
- `GITHUB_CLASSROOM_SETUP.md` — deployment guide
